MobileClaw is an open-source Android AI agent framework. The project builds on
top of many excellent open-source libraries — their respective licenses apply
to those components:

  - Jetpack Compose        Apache 2.0   (Google / AOSP)
  - Ktor                   Apache 2.0   (JetBrains)
  - Room                   Apache 2.0   (Google)
  - OkHttp / Retrofit      Apache 2.0   (Square)
  - Gson                   Apache 2.0   (Google)
  - Coil                   Apache 2.0   (Coil Contributors)
  - Chaquopy Python SDK    MIT          (Chaquopy Contributors)
  - Material Icons         Apache 2.0   (Google / Material Design)

Contributions to MobileClaw are welcome. By submitting a pull request you
agree that your contribution will be licensed under the MIT License and that
you have the right to grant this license.
